#. <section class="sutta" id="an9.2"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an9.2:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.2:0.2"
msgid "1. Sambodhivagga"
msgstr "1. Awakening"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 2. Nissayasutta → nissayasampannasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an9.2:0.3"
msgid "2. Nissayasutta"
msgstr "2. Supported"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.354"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an9.2:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and "
"said to him:"

msgctxt "an9.2:1.2"
msgid "“‘nissayasampanno nissayasampanno’ti, bhante, vuccati."
msgstr "“Sir, they speak of being ‘supported’."

msgctxt "an9.2:1.3"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, bhikkhu nissayasampanno hotī”ti?"
msgstr "How is a mendicant who is supported defined?”"

msgctxt "an9.2:1.4"
msgid ""
"“Saddhañce, bhikkhu, bhikkhu nissāya akusalaṃ pajahati kusalaṃ bhāveti, "
"pahīnamevassa taṃ akusalaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicant, if a mendicant supported by faith gives up the unskillful and "
"develops the skillful, the unskillful is actually given up by them."

msgctxt "an9.2:1.5"
msgid "Hiriñce, bhikkhu, bhikkhu nissāya … pe …"
msgstr "If a mendicant supported by conscience …"

msgctxt "an9.2:1.6"
msgid "ottappañce, bhikkhu, bhikkhu nissāya … pe …"
msgstr "If a mendicant supported by prudence …"

msgctxt "an9.2:1.7"
msgid "vīriyañce, bhikkhu, bhikkhu nissāya … pe …"
msgstr "If a mendicant supported by energy …"

msgctxt "an9.2:1.8"
msgid ""
"paññañce, bhikkhu, bhikkhu nissāya akusalaṃ pajahati kusalaṃ bhāveti, "
"pahīnamevassa taṃ akusalaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"If a mendicant supported by wisdom gives up the unskillful and develops the "
"skillful, the unskillful is actually given up by them."

msgctxt "an9.2:1.9"
msgid ""
"Taṃ hissa bhikkhuno akusalaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti suppahīnaṃ, yaṃsa ariyāya paññāya "
"disvā pahīnaṃ."
msgstr ""
"What’s been given up is completely given up when it has been given up by "
"seeing with noble wisdom."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an9.2:2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena ca pana, bhikkhu, bhikkhunā imesu pañcasu dhammesu patiṭṭhāya cattāro "
"upanissāya vihātabbā."
msgstr "A mendicant grounded on these five things should rely on four things."

msgctxt "an9.2:2.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an9.2:2.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhu, bhikkhu saṅkhāyekaṃ paṭisevati, saṅkhāyekaṃ adhivāseti, "
"saṅkhāyekaṃ parivajjeti, saṅkhāyekaṃ vinodeti."
msgstr ""
"After reflection, a mendicant uses some things, endures some things, avoids "
"some things, and gets rid of some things."

msgctxt "an9.2:2.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, bhikkhu nissayasampanno hotī”ti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is supported.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an9.2:2.5"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
